<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4066.1.3>
    dc:creator "Aguila, Rayner Núñez; Davis, Don R." ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Antillopsyche sessilis, new genus and species, a new Psychidae (Lepidoptera: Tineoidea) from Cuba with an unusual larval feeding behavior" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262611>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262612>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262613>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262614>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262615>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262616>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262617> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262611>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8 – 9. Habitus of Antillophanes cubensis. 8 — Dorsal view of male holotype. CUBA: Granma, Bartolomé Masó, La Aguada de Joaquín, 1300 m. 9 — Dorsal view of female paratype. CUBA: same data. Scale bar 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262611/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262612>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10 – 20. Antillophanes cubensis larval morphology. 10 — Living last instar larva within its case, CUBA: Granma, Bartolomé Masó, La Aguada de Joaquín, 1300 m. 11 — Lateral view of the integumental pigmentation of last instar larva. 12 — Dorsal view of the integumental pigmentation of last instar larva. 13 — Lateral view of prothorax, mesothorax, and abdominal segments 1, 6, 8, and 9. 14 — Dorsal view of head. 15 — Ventral view of head, scale bar 1 mm. 16 — Dorsal view of abdominal segments 8 – 10. 17 — Ocellar region of right side of head. 18 — Ventral view of labrum. 19 — Dorsal view of labrum. 20 — Ventral view of left mandible, scale bar 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262612/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262613>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21 – 22. Antillophanes cubensis pupal morphology. 21 — Ventral view of male pupa. 22 — Dorsal view of male pupa. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262613/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262614>
    dc:description "FIGURES 23 – 24. Antillophanes cubensis larval cases and host fungi. 23 — Larval cases feeding on Trametes villosa (Polyporaceae). 24 — Larvae within their cases feeding on Phylloporia pectinata (Hymenochaetaceae)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262614/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262615>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Geographical distribution of Antillophanes cubensis. Question mark in western Cuba indicating unconfirmed record." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262615/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262616>
    dc:description "FIGURES 26 – 27. Antillophanes cubensis feeding and pupal behavior. 26 — Larval cases attached to a standing dead trunk, left arrow indicating an active feeding larva at distal end, right arrow indicating remains of fungus Trametes villosa. 27 — Extruded pupal exuviae, left case bent by Dryadaula sp. (Dryadaulidae) modification, right case straight in the usual way." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262616/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262617>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28 – 29. 28 — Dryadaula sp. (Dryadaulidae) emerged from Antillophanes cubensis modified larval case, scale bar 1 mm. 29 — Baryscapus sp. (Eulophidae: Tetrastichinae), parasitoid reared from Antillophanes cubensis larva." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262617/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

